cs.PF, cs.AR, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.MS

The paper focuses on performance modeling and optimization of stencil algorithms, which are commonly used in computational science. This makes cs.PF (Performance) the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses memory hierarchy and cache optimization, which are relevant to cs.AR (Architecture) and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions optimization approaches such as spatial blocking and strength reduction, which are related to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
